> Do’s for Responsible Social Media Use
Think before you post—ensure your content is respectful and appropriate
Protect your privacy by limiting personal information shared online
Verify information before sharing to avoid spreading misinformation
Use professional language, especially on platforms like LinkedIn
Respect others’ opinions and engage in healthy discussions
> Don’ts for Responsible Social Media Use
Don’t share offensive, abusive, or harmful content
Don’t post confidential or sensitive information
Don’t engage in cyberbullying or online harassment
Don’t overshare personal details like location or contact info
Don’t post impulsively when emotional (anger, frustration, etc.)
